    "directions": [
      {
        "id": "51-hour-focaccia-directions",
        "title": "Directions",
        "steps": [
          {
            "id": "51-hour-focaccia-step-1",
            "order": 1,
            "text": "In a medium bowl, whisk the instant yeast into the water until dissolved."
          },
          {
            "id": "51-hour-focaccia-step-2",
            "order": 2,
            "text": "In a large bowl, whisk together the tipo 00 flour and fine sea salt until combined. Add the yeast mixture to the flour mixture. Mix by hand until it forms a shaggy dough. With your hand cupped, scoop up the dough and then slap it right back down into the bowl over and over for about 5 minutes, or until the dough begins to smooth out. (This is my preferred method of kneading this style of dough.) Cover the bowl tightly with plastic wrap, and refrigerate for 48 hours."
          },
          {
            "id": "51-hour-focaccia-step-3",
            "order": 3,
            "text": "Generously oil a 9- × 13-inch (23 × 33cm) baking pan with olive oil. A little bit of a pool of oil is desired; somewhere around 1/4 to 1/3 cup (60 to 80ml) of oil is appropriate. Scrape the dough into the baking pan, spreading it as much as possible. Cover with plastic wrap, and let it rest for 15 minutes. Spread the dough out to the edges of the pan. Then cover again with plastic wrap, and proof at room temperature for 3½ hours."
          },
          {
            "id": "51-hour-focaccia-step-4",
            "order": 4,
            "text": "When there’s only 1 hour left of proof time, preheat the oven to its maximum temperature, ideally 500°F (260°C)."
          },
          {
            "id": "51-hour-focaccia-step-5",
            "order": 5,
            "text": "After proofing, generously drizzle extra-virgin olive oil over top of the dough and also add a little in your hands. Rub your hands together, and use your fingertips to dimple the dough all over the surface. Sprinkle the flaky salt and za’atar (if using) on top of the dough. Place the pan in the oven, and bake for 20 to 30 minutes, or until the bread has puffed, is a gorgeous golden brown on the outside, and is just baked through."
          },
          {
            "id": "51-hour-focaccia-step-6",
            "order": 6,
            "text": "Remove the focaccia from the oven, let it cool in the baking pan for 1 minute, and immediately transfer to a wire rack to cool completely so the bottom stays crispy."
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
