    "description": "My first thought when I saw a wedge salad as a kid was, “This is some sort of ancient alien pyramid shape of lettuce that’s been doused in an egregious amount of unidentifiable dressing.” Obviously, there is a way to make this thing tasty and equally beautiful, too. In an effort to correct the experiences of my childhood, we’ll begin with this wedge salad. Oh, and for those of you who’ve probably gasped by now about the lack of bleu cheese dressing, please understand that I hate it. Thank you…that is all.",
