    "description": "A compound butter is a nice culinary term to describe a flavored butter. It’s not only underrated, but it’s also underutilized. If you keep a couple flavored butters in your fridge, you can impart those flavors by adding the butter into a nice sauce, mixing it into your mashed potatoes, or even slathering it on toast to make some garlic bread. You see where I’m going here?",
