    "description": "This recipe has some history for me. By that I mean I don’t really like tuna melts. And by THAT I mean I don’t like MOST tuna melts. I think it’s more the idea of the words tuna melt. Just the name makes me feel funny. So this recipe was developed for two reasons: to create a tuna melt that I would enjoy with gusto, and to satisfy an incessant request for this sandwich from one of my favorite roommates, Allison. So this one’s for you.",
